==Abstract==

This IIP describes the use of mnemonic phrases to generate deterministic wallet seeds. It implements BIP 39 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

A mnemonic phrase (seed phrase) provides:
* Human-readable wallet backup
* Easy transcription and verification
* Standardized wallet recovery

==Specification==

===Mnemonic Generation===

# Generate random entropy (128-256 bits)
# Calculate checksum: SHA256(entropy)[0:entropy_bits/32]
# Append checksum to entropy
# Split into 11-bit groups
# Map each group to a word from the wordlist

===Word Counts===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Entropy (bits) !! Checksum (bits) !! Total (bits) !! Words
|-
| 128 || 4 || 132 || 12
|-
| 160 || 5 || 165 || 15
|-
| 192 || 6 || 198 || 18
|-
| 224 || 7 || 231 || 21
|-
| 256 || 8 || 264 || 24
|}

===Seed Generation===

<pre>
seed = PBKDF2(
    password = mnemonic_words (space-separated, NFKD normalized),
    salt = "mnemonic" + passphrase,
    iterations = 2048,
    key_length = 64,
    hash = SHA512
)
</pre>

===INTcoin HD Derivation===

The 64-byte seed is used with IIP-44 (SHA3-based HD derivation) to generate ML-DSA-87 keys:

<pre>
master_chain_code = SHAKE256(seed || 0x00, 32)
master_key = ML-DSA-87.KeyGen(SHAKE256(seed || 0x01, 64))
</pre>

===Wordlists===

Standard BIP 39 wordlists are supported:
* English (2048 words)
* Japanese, Spanish, Chinese, French, Italian, Korean, Czech, Portuguese

===Passphrase===

An optional passphrase provides:
* Additional security layer
* Plausible deniability (different passphrases → different wallets)

